<ContentLayout title="Hiking" description="Hiking in the Ith-Region: Ith-Hils Trail, themed paths and circular walks in the Weserbergland." heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1551632811-561732d1e306?w=1920&h=800&fit=crop" heroImageAlt="Hiker on a forest trail" heroSubtitle="The Ith-Hils Trail and numerous themed paths invite you to explore">
  <h2>Ith-Hils Trail – Quality Hiking Path</h2>
  <p>The <strong>Ith-Hils Trail</strong> is certified as a <em>Quality Trail</em> and runs for approximately <strong>80 kilometres</strong> along the Ith and Hils ridges in the eastern Weserbergland. The route passes through spectacular rock landscapes, bizarre formations, historic towers and idyllic lake scenery.</p>

  <div class="bg-ith-blue-light rounded-xl p-6 my-8 not-prose">
    <h3 class="text-ith-blue-dark font-bold text-lg mb-3">At a Glance</h3>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 text-sm">
      <div><span class="block text-anthracite-light">Total Length</span><span class="font-semibold text-anthracite">approx. 80 km</span></div>
      <div><span class="block text-anthracite-light">Stages</span><span class="font-semibold text-anthracite">7 stages</span></div>
      <div><span class="block text-anthracite-light">Difficulty</span><span class="font-semibold text-anthracite">Moderate</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h3>Stage 7: Salzhemmendorf – Coppenbrügge</h3>
  <p>The final stage connects the two towns of the Ith-Region. Over <strong>10 kilometres</strong>, the path leads past historic towers, lake landscapes and the spectacular cliffs of the Ith. Walking time is approximately 3 hours.</p>

